# Backend Rules

> Backend-specific rules. Project-wide rules live in `.cursor/rules/core/`.
> Client (frontend) rules: `.cursor/rules/frontend/`.

**Stack:** NestJS · Prisma · PostgreSQL · OpenTelemetry

## Rule Files

When working on backend code, follow **core** rules plus **all** rules in this folder:

| File               | Scope                                                       |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| `core.mdc`         | Public API, imports, exports, types, constants              |
| `architecture.mdc` | Clean Architecture, dependency flow, layer responsibilities |
| `api.mdc`          | DTOs, HTTP status codes, errors, error format               |
| `prisma.mdc`       | Prisma Client, migrations, repository data access           |
| `performance.mdc`  | Query efficiency, N+1                                       |
| `checklist.mdc`    | Pre-completion verification                                 |

## Priority

`checklist.mdc` applies on task completion. Among domain rules:

`api.mdc` > `architecture.mdc` > `core.mdc` > `.cursor/rules/core/*`

## Backend Scope

```
apps/server/           # NestJS application
packages/database/     # Prisma schema, client, migrations
```

## Checklist

Before finishing a backend task, see `checklist.mdc`. Key conventions (`core.mdc`):

- [ ] Module has root `index.ts` public API
- [ ] Imports go through module public API only (`@/layer/module`)
- [ ] Named exports only
